      "text": "The molecular formula $\\text{C}_{16}\\text{H}_{13}\\text{F}_3\\text{O}_2\\text{Se}$ and the NMR data indicate the presence of two distinct aromatic systems linked by a selenomethyl bridge. The first system is a $p$-methoxybenzyl group, identified by the characteristic AA'BB' doublet pattern in the $^1\\text{H}$ NMR ($\\delta$ 7.20 and 6.82), a methoxy singlet ($\\delta$ 3.79), and a benzylic methylene singlet ($\\delta$ 4.15). The second system is a 1,2,4-trisubstituted benzene ring, containing an aldehyde group ($\\delta$ 10.18), a trifluoromethyl group, and the selenium linkage.\n\nSpecifically, the trisubstituted ring shows an ortho-coupled pair of protons ($\\delta$ 7.92 and 7.60, $J \\approx 8.0$ Hz) and one singlet proton ($\\delta$ 7.79). In the $^{13}\\text{C}$ NMR, the presence of two CH carbons showing small C-F couplings ($J \\approx 4$ Hz) confirms that the $\\text{CF}_3$ group is positioned such that two aromatic CH groups are ortho to it, which is consistent with the $\\text{CF}_3$ being at the 4-position in a 1,2,4-trisubstituted benzene (ortho to positions 3 and 5). The aldehyde is assigned to the 1-position (ortho to the H6 doublet at $\\delta$ 7.92), and the selenium substituent is at the 2-position (ortho to the H3 singlet at $\\delta$ 7.79).\n\nFINAL_RESULT:\n  UUID: ebcfa349-c56f-4ce1-90f7-924dea104f59\n  PREDICTED_SMILES: COc1ccc(C[Se]c2cc(C(F)(F)F)ccc2C=O)cc1\n  CONFIDENCE: 0.95\n  REASON_BRIEF: The structure was elucidated as 2-((4-methoxybenzyl)selanyl)-4-(trifluoromethyl)benzaldehyde based on the identification of the p-methoxybenzyl and 2,4-disubstituted benzaldehyde fragments through 1H and 13C NMR. The 1,2,4-substitution pattern and CF3 placement were confirmed by proton multiplicities and C-F coupling constants.",
